<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" />
    <title>How to make fried rice</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="recipe-card">
      <p class="badge">Quick & cozy lunch</p>
      <h1>How to make fried rice</h1>
      <p class="intro">
        Fried rice is a crowd-pleasing dish that turns simple ingredients into something
        bright, savory, and satisfying. This version is fast, fun, and perfect for lunch.
      </p>

      <section class="ingredients">
        <h2>What you need</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Rice:</strong> 3–4 cups of chilled leftover cooked rice</li>
          <li><strong>Eggs:</strong> 2–3 whisked eggs</li>
          <li><strong>Veggies:</strong> carrots, peas, onions, and garlic</li>
          <li><strong>Flavor:</strong> soy sauce, oil, and a dash of sesame oil if you like</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="steps">
        <h2>Steps</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Start with cold rice so it stays fluffy instead of mushy.</li>
          <li>Heat oil in a skillet and sauté the veggies and garlic until fragrant.</li>
          <li>Push everything to one side, then scramble the eggs in the empty space.</li>
          <li>Add the rice and stir-fry until the grains are hot and lightly toasted.</li>
          <li>Pour in the soy sauce, toss everything together, and serve immediately.</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <div class="visual" aria-hidden="true">🍚</div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
